attributes.gcd: Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.

Refers to the business key of delivery location identifier. The reference table for this column is Stage Address Master (Address Identifier). In case of Freight Commodities, the delivery address will be same as Destination Address.

Refers to the location from where the freight has started its journey or the starting point according to the contract. For e.g.. If the route is (C5) West Australia to Qingdao, this column will hold the identifier for West Australia. The reference table(column) for this column Stage Address Master (Address Identifier).
Refers to the date on which the freight reaches/arrives at the destination location.

Refers to the destination location for the freight or the ending/destination location according to the contract. For e.g.. If the route is (C5) West Australia to Qingdao, this column will hold the identifier for Qingdao. The reference table(column) for this column is Stage Address Master (Address Identifier).
Refers to a unique Code representing a particular Instrument. This code can be ISIN Code, CUSIP, SEDOL etc. Instrument Contract dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.
Refers to the production region or location code for Electricity and carbon trading commodities. For e.g. Electricity NE denotes electricity produced in North East Region and so on.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.
Refers to the run identifier for a set of Records participating in the particular Run with the Run Execution identifier. This is a combination of Run Main Identifier and Run Execution Identifier.
Refers to the date on which the freight left the embark location or started its journey.
Refers to the via location for the freight. For e.g. Suez Canal. The reference table for this column is Stage Address Master (Address Identifier).
